ABUJA  – Nigeria is to collaborate with the Republic of Cuba in the development of biotechnology for food and pharmaceutical production. Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu, Minister of Science, Technology and Innovation this known when the Ambassador of Cuba to Nigeria, Amb. Clara Pulido Escadell paid him a courtesy visit in his office on Monday in Abuja. Dr. Onu said that Nigeria which has a large youthful population as compared to other developed countries would accelerate the development of the country especially in the areas of biotechnology. He further said that Nigerian youths both at home and in the Diaspora, have reached the peak of their careers in various technological endeavours and that with the necessary skills, they could take Nigeria to greater heights. On food security, he said the Federal Government is no longer one of the largest importers of rice, but has emerged as one of the largest producers and exporters of rice in Africa. Onu assured the Cuban envoy of Nigeria’s collaboration and close working relationship with the country. Clara Pulido Escadell the Ambassador of Cuba to Nigeria, said her visit was to discuss Nigeria’s participation in the forthcoming International Conference Bio Habana 2022, slated for 25th-29th April, 2022 in Cuba. She also discussed the relationship between the two nations and hailed the tremendous opportunities that abound in Nigeria.